Evidence: "The drugs most often used in the OBR were tenofovir (79%, either as TAF [53%] or as tenofovir disoproxil fumarate [26%]), FTC (68%), DRV (61%), DTG (50%), doravirine (26%), and IBA (24%)."
Rationale: The paper lists the drugs most often used in the optimized background regimen (OBR) for the study participants.
Answer: Tenofovir (TFV), Emtricitabine (FTC), Darunavir (DRV), Dolutegravir (DTG), Doravirine (DOR), Ibalizumab (IBA), Lenacapavir (LEN)
